# Helpers CLI staging
.helpers/

# helpers-lock.json — safety guard for THIS repo (upstream) only.
# Upstream is the SOURCE of the template, not a consumer — so if someone
# accidentally runs `clai-helpers init` inside this clone, the generated
# lockfile must not sneak into a commit.
#
# Consumer repos (downstream projects that use clai-helpers) MUST commit
# their helpers-lock.json — same convention as package-lock.json. The lock
# encodes: which upstream version was synced, file checksums for drift
# detection, and protected-slot hashes. Without it, `clai-helpers status
# --strict` breaks and team members drift out of sync on every local run.
helpers-lock.json